----------------------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This example creates a layered mesh with an oceanic layer on top, 
two compacted sediment layers in the middle (poroelastic material) overlaying an elastic bottom layer.
It therefore couples both an acoustic (fluid) and an elastic layer with poroelastic layers.

The example follows the setup presented in Morency et al. (2008), figure 14, 
but extends the model to 3D and enlarges the source-receiver distances.

To run the simulation, type:

> ./run_this_example.sh

which uses the in-house mesher xmeshfem3D to create the mesh layout, or

> ./run_this_example.sh 1

to use the provided Cubit/Trelis mesh in MESH-default/ with a mesh partitioner (Scotch).

Compare your seismograms in OUTPUT_FILES/ with the reference ones in directory REF_SEIS/

